{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775856925571,"sessionID":"ses_286ade9b8ffe345JXsiaQtvma3","part":{"id":"prt_d79523b7f001SABiBXBAqARE5U","messageID":"msg_d7952301700143HLfPvJfccB8r","sessionID":"ses_286ade9b8ffe345JXsiaQtvma3","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"text","timestamp":1775856962379,"sessionID":"ses_286ade9b8ffe345JXsiaQtvma3","part":{"id":"prt_d79524d2d001NI5TONOiAkL2kV","messageID":"msg_d7952301700143HLfPvJfccB8r","sessionID":"ses_286ade9b8ffe345JXsiaQtvma3","type":"text","text":"I'll create a delta-spec.md for AR-014 focusing on the Valkey storage implementation scenarios.","time":{"start":1775856962374,"end":1775856962374}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775856962394,"sessionID":"ses_286ade9b8ffe345JXsiaQtvma3","part":{"id":"prt_d7952cb49001EaaSvueeDftGcr","messageID":"msg_d7952301700143HLfPvJfccB8r","sessionID":"ses_286ade9b8ffe345JXsiaQtvma3","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-f9dbd9b8f1cc492881335d250fc11129","state":{"status":"error","input":{"content":"# Delta Specification: AR-014 — Valkey 存储实现\n\n## Overview\n\nThis delta specification describes scenarios for implementing Valkey as a backend for the session store, adding Valkey support alongside the existing Redis implementation.\n\n## Module\n\n- `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/store`\n\n## Language\n\nGo\n\n## Size\n\nS\n\n---\n\n## Requirements and Scenarios\n\n### Requirement: Valkey client initialization\n\nThe system SHALL initialize a Valkey client using `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go` when `STORE_TYPE=valkey` (case-insensitive).\n\n#### Scenario: Default to Redis when STORE_TYPE unset\n- **GIVEN** `STORE_TYPE` environment variable is not set\n- **WHEN** `Storage()` is called for the first time\n- **THEN** Redis store is initialized\n- **AND** `redisStoreType` is used\n\n#### Scenario: Valkey selected by STORE_TYPE\n- **GIVEN** `STORE_TYPE=valkey` (case-insensitive)\n- **WHEN** `initStore()` runs\n- **THEN** Valkey store is initialized\n- **AND** `valkeyStoreType` is used\n\n#### Scenario: Invalid STORE_TYPE causes fatal error\n- **GIVEN** `STORE_TYPE=mongodb`\n- **WHEN** `initStore()` attempts to determine store type\n- **THEN** initialization fails with fatal error logged via klog\n\n### Requirement: Valkey connection configuration\n\nThe system SHALL configure Valkey client using environment variables with Valkey-specific options.\n\n#### Scenario: Single address configuration\n- **GIVEN** `VALKEY_ADDR=localhost:7379`\n- **WHEN** `makeValkeyOptions()` constructs options\n- **THEN** `InitAddress` is `[]string{\"localhost:7379\"}`\n\n#### Scenario: Multiple addresses configuration\n- **GIVEN** `VALKEY_ADDR=node1:7379,node2:7379,node3:7379`\n- **WHEN** `makeValkeyOptions()` constructs options\n- **THEN** `InitAddress` is `[]string{\"node1:7379\", \"node2:7379\", \"node3:7379\"}`\n\n#### Scenario: Password required by default\n- **GIVEN** `VALKEY_ADDR` set\n- **AND** `VALKEY_PASSWORD` empty\n- **AND** `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` unset or not \"false\"\n- **WHEN** Valkey client is initialized\n- **THEN** initialization fails with error stating password required\n\n#### Scenario: Password optional when disabled\n- **GIVEN** `VALKEY_ADDR` set\n- **AND** `VALKEY_PASSWORD` empty\n- **AND** `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false`\n- **WHEN** Valkey client is initialized\n- **THEN** client is created without password\n- **AND** `ClientOption.Password` is empty string\n\n#### Scenario: Password provided\n- **GIVEN** `VALKEY_PASSWORD=secret123`\n- **WHEN** Valkey client is initialized\n- **THEN** `ClientOption.Password` is \"secret123\"\n\n### Requirement: Valkey optional client flags\n\nThe system SHALL support optional Valkey client configuration via environment variables.\n\n#### Scenario: Disable cache enabled\n- **GIVEN** `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE=true`\n- **WHEN** `makeValkeyOptions()` constructs options\n- **THEN** `ClientOption.DisableCache` is true\n\n#### Scenario: Disable cache not set\n- **GIVEN** `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE` unset\n- **WHEN** `makeValkeyOptions()` constructs options\n- **THEN** `ClientOption.DisableCache` is false (default)\n\n#### Scenario: Force single client enabled\n- **GIVEN** `VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE=true`\n- **WHEN** `makeValkeyOptions()` constructs options\n- **THEN** `ClientOption.ForceSingleClient` is true\n\n#### Scenario: Force single client not set\n- **GIVEN** `VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE` unset\n- **WHEN** `makeValkeyOptions()` constructs options\n- **THEN** `ClientOption.ForceSingleClient` is false (default)\n\n### Requirement: Valkey Ping operation\n\nThe system SHALL verify Valkey connectivity using the Valkey API.\n\n#### Scenario: Successful ping\n- **GIVEN** a healthy Valkey server\n- **WHEN** `Ping(ctx)` is called\n- **THEN** `B().Ping()` is executed\n- **AND** result string equals \"PONG\"\n- **AND** error is nil\n\n#### Scenario: Ping connection failure\n- **GIVEN** Valkey server is unreachable\n- **WHEN** `Ping(ctx)` is called\n- **THEN** error is returned from Valkey client\n\n### Requirement: Valkey GetSandboxBySessionID\n\nThe system SHALL retrieve sandbox data using Valkey Get API with nil detection.\n\n#### Scenario: Retrieve existing session\n- **GIVEN** key `session:abc` exists with valid JSON\n- **WHEN** `GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, \"abc\")` is called\n- **THEN** `B().Get().Key(\"session:abc\")` returns JSON bytes\n- **AND** JSON unmarshals to `*types.SandboxInfo`\n- **AND** error is nil\n\n#### Scenario: Get missing session returns ErrNotFound\n- **GIVEN** key `session:xyz` does not exist\n- **WHEN** `GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, \"xyz\")` is called\n- **THEN** `B().Get()` returns bytes with `IsValkeyNil` true\n- **AND** error is `ErrNotFound`\n\n### Requirement: Valkey StoreSandbox\n\nThe system SHALL store sandbox data using Valkey DoMulti pipeline with SETNX and ZADD operations.\n\n#### Scenario: Successful store with all operations\n- **GIVEN** a valid `SandboxInfo` with non-zero `ExpiresAt`\n- **WHEN** `StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` is called\n- **THEN** `DoMulti` executes in order:\n  - `SETNX session:{id} {json}`\n  - `ZADD session:expiry {ExpiresAt.Unix()} {id}`\n  - `ZADD session:last_activity {now.Unix()} {id}`\n- **AND** error is nil\n\n#### Scenario: Nil sandbox rejected\n- **GIVEN** `StoreSandbox(ctx, nil)` is called\n- **WHEN** validation runs\n- **THEN** error indicates sandbox is nil\n- **AND** no Valkey operations are executed\n\n#### Scenario: Zero ExpiresAt rejected\n- **GIVEN** `SandboxInfo` with `ExpiresAt.IsZero()` true\n- **WHEN** `StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` is called\n- **THEN** error indicates invalid expires at\n- **AND** no Valkey operations are executed\n\n#### Scenario: Pipeline operation fails\n- **GIVEN** Valkey connection fails during DoMulti\n- **WHEN** `StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` is called\n- **THEN** error is returned from Valkey client\n- **AND** no partial writes are committed\n\n### Requirement: Valkey UpdateSandbox\n\nThe system SHALL update existing sandbox using SET with XX flag.\n\n#### Scenario: Update existing session\n- **GIVEN** key `session:abc` exists\n- **WHEN** `UpdateSandbox(ctx, updated)` is called\n- **THEN** `SET session:abc {json} XX` is executed\n- **AND** `ToString()` result equals \"OK\"\n- **AND** error is nil\n\n#### Scenario: Update missing session fails\n- **GIVEN** key `session:xyz` does not exist\n- **WHEN** `UpdateSandbox(ctx, updated)` is called\n- **THEN** `SET ... XX` does not create the key\n- **AND** `ToString()` result is not \"OK\"\n- **AND** error indicates key not exists\n\n### Requirement: Valkey DeleteSandboxBySessionID\n\nThe system SHALL delete session and remove from both ZSETs using DoMulti.\n\n#### Scenario: Delete existing session\n- **GIVEN** session `abc` exists in all three keys\n- **WHEN** `DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx, \"abc\")` is called\n- **THEN** `DoMulti` executes:\n  - `DEL session:abc`\n  - `ZREM session:expiry abc`\n  - `ZREM session:last_activity abc`\n- **AND** error is nil\n\n#### Scenario: Delete non-existent session\n- **GIVEN** session `xyz` does not exist\n- **WHEN** `DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx, \"xyz\")` is called\n- **THEN** all operations are executed\n- **AND** error is nil (idempotent)\n\n### Requirement: Valkey ListExpiredSandboxes\n\nThe system SHALL query expiry index using Valkey Zrangebyscore and fetch documents via Mget.\n\n#### Scenario: List with limit > 0\n- **GIVEN** `ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, before, 100)`\n- **AND** `before.Unix()` = 1710000000\n- **WHEN** method executes\n- **THEN** `Zrangebyscore` is called on `session:expiry`\n- **AND** `Min(\"-inf\")` and `Max(\"1710000000\")`\n- **AND** `Limit(0, 100)` is applied\n- **AND** all returned session IDs are fetched via `Mget`\n- **AND** valid JSON documents are unmarshaled\n\n#### Scenario: List with limit <= 0 returns nil\n- **GIVEN** `ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, before, 0)`\n- **WHEN** method executes\n- **THEN** no Valkey operations are executed\n- **AND** result is `nil, nil`\n\n#### Scenario: Orphan ZSET member skipped\n- **GIVEN** ZSET contains session id `orphan`\n- **AND** key `session:orphan` does not exist\n- **WHEN** `Mget` returns empty for that key\n- **THEN** `orphan` is omitted from result slice\n- **AND** other valid sessions are included\n\n### Requirement: Valkey ListInactiveSandboxes\n\nThe system SHALL query last_activity index with same semantics as expiry list.\n\n#### Scenario: List inactive sessions\n- **GIVEN** `ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx, before, 50)`\n- **WHEN** method executes\n- **THEN** `Zrangebyscore` is called on `session:last_activity`\n- **AND** same Min/Max/Limit semantics as expiry list\n- **AND** documents fetched via `Mget`\n\n### Requirement: Valkey UpdateSessionLastActivity\n\nThe system SHALL verify key exists before updating activity timestamp.\n\n#### Scenario: Activity bump for existing session\n- **GIVEN** key `session:abc` exists\n- **AND** `at` = 2024-04-10T12:00:00Z\n- **WHEN** `UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, \"abc\", at)` is called\n- **THEN** `Exists().Key(\"session:abc\")` returns 1\n- **AND** `Zadd session:last_activity {at.Unix()} abc` is executed\n- **AND** error is nil\n\n#### Scenario: Activity bump for missing session returns ErrNotFound\n- **GIVEN** key `session:xyz` does not exist\n- **WHEN** `UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, \"xyz\", at)` is called\n- **THEN** `Exists()` returns 0\n- **AND** `Zadd` is not executed\n- **AND** error is `ErrNotFound`\n\n#### Scenario: Empty session id rejected\n- **GIVEN** empty string as session id\n- **WHEN** `UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, \"\", at)` is called\n- **THEN** error indicates invalid session id\n- **AND** no Valkey operations are executed\n\n#### Scenario: Zero time uses current time\n- **GIVEN** existing session `abc`\n- **AND** `at.IsZero()` true\n- **WHEN** `UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, \"abc\", at)` is called\n- **THEN** `Zadd` score uses `time.Now().Unix()`\n\n### Requirement: Valkey Close\n\nThe system SHALL close Valkey client connection.\n\n#### Scenario: Successful close\n- **GIVEN** open Valkey client\n- **WHEN** `Close()` is called\n- **THEN** `vs.cli.Close()` is executed\n- **AND** error is nil\n\n---\n\n## Differences from Redis Implementation\n\n| Aspect | Redis | Valkey |\n|--------|-------|--------|\n| Client library | `github.com/redis/go-redis/v9` | `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go` |\n| Ping method | `Ping(ctx)` returns `PONG` via command result | `B().Ping()` returns string |\n| Get nil detection | `redis.Nil` error | `IsValkeyNil()` on bytes result |\n| Pipeline/Multi | `cli.Pipeline()` or `TxPipeline()` | `DoMulti()` with multiple commands |\n| SETXX success check | Boolean result | `ToString() == \"OK\"` |\n| ZRANGEBYSCORE | Client method with `RangeBy` options | `Zrangebyscore` with `Min()`, `Max()`, `Limit()` |\n| Batch GET | `cli.MGet(keys)` | `Mget(keys)` |\n| Key existence | `cli.Exists(ctx, key)` | `Exists().Key(key)` |\n| Address config | Single `Addr` string | `InitAddress` string slice |\n| Optional flags | None | `DisableCache`, `ForceSingleClient` |","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/delta-spec.md"},"error":"You must read file /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/delta-spec.md before overwriting it. Use the Read tool first","time":{"start":1775856962385,"end":1775856962390}}}}
